Date: 20/10/1864
Source: Chudleigh Diary
Author:
Vol / Page: 149
Edition: 1950
Quote: Mr Acland and I went to the wash pen in the morning. They have been washing since Monday and will be at it all next week. On Tuesday a large bird flew over the pen. All hands and the cook took after it ... a black swan was captured.
Notes:

Date: 10/11/1860
Source: Nelson Examiner and New Zealand Chronicle
Author:
Vol / Page: 2
Edition:
Quote: There seems to be a growing disposition among flockowners to shear their flocks in the grease, under the impresssion [sic] that unless they are able to get up their wool in a really creditable manner, it is useless to wash their sheep at all, and without properly constructed washing pens, and suitable paddocks, conveniences which few of them as yet possess, it is better not to make the attempt.
